+/**
+ * @ingroup system-tests-tc
+ *
+ * Verify that EnableHostIsolation composes correctly with the byte-counted
+ * MemLimit admission gate. With both engaged, the MemLimit cap must continue
+ * to enforce the byte ceiling under sustained single-flow arrivals, and the
+ * per-host bookkeeping introduced by host-isolation must not bypass or
+ * inflate the byte accounting.
+ *
+ * A FqCobaltQueueDisc is configured with MemLimit=500 and
+ * EnableHostIsolation=true under HostIsolationMode::Triple. Twenty
+ * ~120-byte items (100 B payload + 20 B IPv4 header) arrive from a single
+ * (src,dst) pair. All arrivals are admitted (Linux-faithful MemLimit has
+ * no pre-enqueue gate); the post-everything eviction loop bounds the
+ * final byte total at the cap. The host-isolation accounting must still
+ * be coherent across the eviction path (per-host bulk-flow counters
+ * decremented when a flow drains via eviction).
